[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * <p>This combines calls to {@link #findMethodExact(Class, String, Object...)} and
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * {@link XposedBridge#hookMethod}.
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     *
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * <p class="warning">The method must be declared or overridden in the given class, inherited
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * methods are not considered! That's because each method implementation exists only once in
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * the memory, and when classes inherit it, they just get another reference to the implementation.
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * Hooking a method therefore applies to all classes inheriting the same implementation. You
