[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * or {@code Integer.TYPE}. Note that {@code Integer.class} doesn't refer to {@code int} but to
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * {@code Integer}, which is a normal class (boxed primitive). Therefore it must not be used when
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * the method expects an {@code int} parameter - it has to be used for {@code Integer} parameters
[external][tehcneko][7764726+tehcneko@users.noreply.github.com]     * though, so check the method signature in detail.
